        The IT Operations Control will Console Operations, Monitoring, & Routine System Maintenance
        We strive for every interaction to be driven by our CORE values: Insightful Expertise, Integrity is Everything, Service Excellence, Inspiring Innovation, Each Person Counts, Results-Driven, & Social Responsibility.
        RESPONSIBILITIES:
        * Event Management. Manages changes in state of IT Infrastructure leveraging alert systems and tools. Triage based on Run Book. Escalates to Tier II operations support. Oversees the execution and monitoring of all operational activities and events in the IT infrastructure. Manages routine maintenance, scheduled tasks, and cyclical business operations including backups, recycles, and restarts. Supports business back-office operations. Accountable for all hardware break fix coordinating support with vendors, data centers, and implementation engineering. Maintains operations logs/reports, shift schedule logs/reports, and scheduled reports.
        * Availability Management. Monitors technology performance 24/7/365 with accountability to business users, clients, and service managers for service availability. Understands business requirements and cycles escalating utilization, throughput, and maintenance window concerns. Measures and reports on availability. Analyzes information and identifies trends. Provides feedback to implementation engineering and service management on alert thresholds.
        * Continuity Management. Supports disaster recovery testing efforts. Supplies feedback to design engineering in post test reviews. Executes standard recovery procedures in the case of true disaster declaration.
        * Capacity Management. Monitors technology performance during business use cycles with accountability for meeting capacity demands. Triages performance and capacity issues based on Run Book prescribed instruction. Escalates to Technical & Applications Management and/or Implementation Engineering as required. Provides feedback on capacity concerns and observed trends. Performs health checks.
        * Change Coordination: Reviews changes for impact to maintenance windows. Activates/Inactivates monitoring and alerting in conjunction with change. * Communicates scheduled downtime to business users, clients, and service management. * Accountable for authorizing changes on behalf of operations. * Performs post implementation reviews on all change orders as directed by implementation engineering and tier II operations. * Manages premise based hardware coordinating all preparation, configuration, and installation. Accountable for inventories and maintenance schedules. Updates Asset Management and CMDB records accordingly. Supports provisioning and de-provisioning of on premise devices through lifecycle including any required turn-up configuration for ADP Command Centers and Data Centers. * Maintains the escalation database. Performs periodic tests of emergency broadcast
        * Request Fulfillment. * Provide a channel for users to request and receive standard services. Fulfill standard requests relating to operations. Reset, recycle, start/stop services, and execute procedures, jobs, and tasks as directed by the requestor. * Handle inquiries and issues from business units relating to IT Infrastructure Operations, service availability, and performance. Triage those requiring escalation handling transfer as appropriate.
        * Platform Support/Patch Management. * Installs patches according to scheduled maintenance plans ensuring successful deployment. * Manages exceptions to deployments, installs and scheduled upgrades. Escalates to Technical & Application Management as required.
        * Compliance. Executes procedures, maintains records, and captures activities in accordance with policy and audit guidelines. Accountable for compliance. Tracks remediation of non-conformance. Works with internal audit on remediation plans.
        QUALIFICATIONS REQUIRED:
        * Must have excellent Customer Service skills
        * 3+ years experience within IT service & support
        * Must have excellent communication skills, written & verbal
        * Must be able to work weekday nights and/or weekend nights. Must be able to be shift flexible
        * Must have experience with Networking, Windows, and Linux
        * Must have experience with general IT topics client/server, OS, Database, networking, security, and automation.
